image_analysis.description: A photograph taken from a doorway looking into a narrow bathroom or powder room. The room features light-colored wood flooring, beige walls, and a drop-ceiling with recessed lighting. A white toilet and a curved white vanity with a sink are visible. On the left wall, there are two framed pictures. On the back wall, above the toilet, there are two more framed pictures; the lower one has a black redaction box over a portion of the image. The door in the foreground is white with a silver handle and hinge.
image_analysis.layout: Interior architectural photograph with a vertical orientation.

notes: The image contains a black redaction box over one of the framed pictures on the back wall. The text 'EFTA00000366' is a Bates stamp likely added for legal or investigative documentation purposes.
